ant low-propensity items.","method":"Analyzes an iterative training-and-recommendation process under a categorical model of nodes, proving that naive training skews recommendations toward high-propensity categories with high probability and at a rate depending on the ratio of propensity-weighted link probabilities. Shows theoretically and via simulation that correcting for exposure (using the proposed estimators) stabilizes recommendation proportions, mitigating the feedback loop and maintaining exposure to relevant low-propensity items."}]}
